  						<table border='0' cellpadding='3' cellspacing='0' width='92%'>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' align='center'>EVERQUEST: THE CRIMSONBLADE CHRONICLES: CHAPTER THREE</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>    I woke up the next morning very well rested, I got up and stumbled toward the kitchen, where father was sitting at the table with a note in his hands and a worried look on his face, “Hey pop”, I said cheerfully.  “Son….I have something important to tell you….I must go to Freeport.”, I didn’t know what to say, I knew that he would never go there unless something serious was happening.  “Huh…why?”, I said, “That isn’t of any importance to you…just stay here and take care of the house, I will be gone for a while.”  I was saddened, and in a weird way kind of excited, “Alright pop, ill be sure to take care of the house.”  We hugged each other then just like that he was on a horse, with minor supplies in a pouch, and he was gone.
	It had been a year and still he never came back, Reana and I took a liking to each other and we traveled down to the aquaducts, along with Jerome, and killed more cubes, skeletons, and the occasional thug that tried to rob us.  Never did we even see any signs of necromancers or shadow knights, or any thing else, besides the skeletons, that even suggested that they lived down there.  But I knew better.
	Another year passed, still no sign of father.  “Darkire, I’m sure he is fine, don’t worry.”  Said Reana in a comforting tone.  “Yea….I cant help but worry though.” And suddenly I got an idea, “I am going to go to Freeport and find my father.”  “Are you sure you are ready to take that journey, Darkire?”, said Jerome, “Yes!” I said with confidence, “Well you can count me in”, I was glad to hear my that my friend was worried as well, “Me too!” said Reana with a smile.  “Great, get your things, lets meet at the North Qeynos gate tomorrow morning bright and early.” I could tell this was going to be a great journey indeed.
	I got up early that morning, and woke up Reana, who was sleeping beside me, and we got our things and headed to the gate to wait on Jerome.
While at the gate we stood and watched the young warriors, paladins, clerics, casters, and even some evil people that we couldn’t touch because the guards would sure have our heads if we hurt a citizen of Qeynos, even if they were evil.  “Darkire, you never talk about your mother……who was she?”, I was kind of saddened of the memories I had of her….which were no memories, I didn’t have a clue about her, just what my father had told me, “Well, I was very young when she passed away, I don’t remember anything about her, but my father told me that she was the most beautiful person in the world, and that she loved me very much, so Reana, what about your parents?”, “My parents?  Well, they are your typical Erudites who frown upon ignorance, but they were friends with Jerome’s parents, I am still not sure why them and not any other people from Qeynos, hmm, oh well, anyway, Jerome and I met when we visited here about two years ago, and I came back when my parents told me to go find and study ancient runes and tomes of all the world, so I ended up here.”  Whew, when that girl talked, she talked on forever….I guess that was one of the many reasons I liked her.  “Hey guys, are we all ready?”, it was Jerome, “Yes, shall we go then?”, we started on our way, we would have rode horses but they all were either killed or stolen by the gnolls a few weeks ago.
	When we reached the hills and were on our way to the plains of the Karanas, we passed by a camp of gnolls, we tried to sneak by but they seen us, so we dropped our things, picked up our gear and got ready for battle…. The gnolls growled at us fiercely, drew their swords and charged at us shouting “For the glory of Blackburro, your blood shall spill!”, two of them jumped at me but I doged out of the way and then Reana started to cast the spell “root”, the gnoll she casted it on stopped and stood there as roots began to crawl around his feet, and he couldn’t move, Jerome swung his mace at an unsuspecting gnoll, knocking it to the ground where he then blasted it with a holy bolt of some kind, killing it on the spot.  As for me, well, I wasn’t going to let them have all the fun so I ran forward with blades in hand and sliced one of the gnolls in the gut, and spun the Crimsonblade around and stabbed it in the back, it let out a scream of pain and fell to the ground.  As for the rooted gnoll it got free and started to run, but Reana seen him and blasted him with a fire bolt.  The gnoll’s fur caught on fire and it ran screaming into Blacburro.  We came out of the fight with only a few cuts and bruises, but Jerome fixed those up real fast with just a few words.
	We headed out to the Karanas, and met up with Brother Trintle, a cleric of Nife, we talked with him and he offered us a safe place to stay for the night, we accepted and sat down around a fire and talked, Reana fell asleep with her head in my lap.  Jerome and Trintle got along very well, as for me I didn’t understand what they were talking about so I went to sleep.  I could hear Trintle and Jerome talking until I fell asleep.  I awoke the next morning, and everyone else was already up, I could smell something delicious cooking on the fire so I sat up and asked, “Mmm, smells good, what is it?”  “Its about time you woke up, Brother Trintle and I are fixing some bear meat.” Jerome said smiling, I knew he liked bear meat, and so did I, “Great, when is it gonna be ready?” “In just a moment”, said Trintle as he got some wooden bowls out of his backpack.  Reana was sitting calmly beside the fire reading some scrolls written in Erudin, I believe.  I didn’t want to bother her so I left her alone and stood up and stretched.
	“Mmmm, I’ve never had bear before, it was wonderful,” grinned Reana.  “Yes indeed it was”, said Jerome, boasting about his cooking, “well Brother Trintle, we thank thee for your hospitality”, I said with a smile, “T’was nothing sire.”  He said.  “We must be on our way though, good luck to you”, I said.  Trintle bowed and waved goodbye to us and we started down the path towards Highhold pass, a small city occupied by humans who were allies with Qeynos.  I have heard that they have a bad Gnoll and Goblin problem, secretly I had hoped we would run into some and kill them, I don’t know why but I love battle.  I took a swig of brandy as we walked by a stone marker that pointed into the direction of Highhold, and said “We are almost to the mountain where we climb to get to Highhold”, Reana had a worried look on her face, “Don’t worry Reana there is a path, we wont have to climb up anything,”  She let out a sigh of relief and smiled, “Good, because I am not much of a climber”.
	“Woa, look out!”, We all three dropped to the ground as a Griffon flew over our heads.  The Griffon seemed to be running away from whomever it was that warned us, and all of the sudden an Elvin man ran by, drew his bow and shot into the Griffon, and hit it straight on right in the side, it fell and he smiled.  “Thank you kind sir,” I said, “Yea no problem,” he ran to the Griffon and looted some things off of it.  He looked at us and kneeled and then ran away with the speed of a wolf, clearly he was a Ranger, and had casted the spell “Spirit of the Wolf” on himself.  “That was close,” Jerome said, “Lets go.”
	We started up the twisted path up the mountain, I could tell my companions were getting tired, “Look guys, there is a building of some kind over there, lets go take a look and if it is safe lets camp there.”  “Whew, I thought you would never ask,” said Jerome with a tired tone.  We walked up to the building and before we reached it I suddenly felt my feet adhere to the ground, with twisting roots wrapping around my ankles.  “Uh oh guys, look out there is someone here who seems to not want to welcome us.”  I felt a sudden shock of lighting ark through my veins, it made me drop to the ground.  “Quick, find who is casting that…..” I said with pain, Jerome uttered something under his breath and then I felt my wounds disappear, I pulled the Crimsonblade out and started to hack away the roots.  “I will teach you to interfere with me Darkire!” said a half-elf that looked rugged and was casting the spells, I guessed he was a Druid, a bandit druid.  Reana started chanting some words I couldn’t understand, then with a movement of her hand the roots disappeared and I charged at the druid and swung with lighting speed and cut into the druids skin, “Arrggg……”, the druid moaned and then casted a spell on himself that healed his wounds, he swung with his scimitar and barely missed the side of my head, Jerome chanted something and then I felt my muscles get bigger, my speed enhanced, my vitality increased, I lunged at the druid and with three quick swings the druid was on the ground, “My comrades will avenge my death,” he uttered as I took the final blow.
	“Well, that was interesting…I believe he was a bandit,” I said, “Yes, I am glad that ended well, we almost lost you my friend,” said Jerome with worry, “Yes, but I have you two to thank, you saved my life,” I smiled, “Lets set up camp in here,” I motioned to the one room tower in which the druid had stayed in.”  We set up a fire and set up a spit, “I will be right back, I am going to go get us something to eat,” I got up and started to leave, “Ok, but hurry back,” said Reana.  I nodded, and started out to the path, I took a glance down the path, I did not see anything, I looked up the path and could see a figure, I think it is on all fours…but I wasn’t sure.  I walked slowly up the path, once I got up to a close enough distance to see the animal I noticed it was a wolf of some kind, now I don’t like to eat wolf but if there is nothing else then it will have to do.  I crept up behind the wolf and raised my sword, “That would not be very wise sire,” I froze, the wolf had spoken to me, it turned around and said, “I would not attack me, it would mean big trouble for you,” “I am sorry, I didn’t realize……my camp is just down the path, we needed something to eat…”  I said, “I see, well I have a camp up the path a little ways, if you and your companions would like to join us.”  I was honored to have someone I almost attacked to invite me to his camp, “thank you kind sir…or…err..ma’am?”  The wolf started to take the shape of a woman, an Elf, “I am Frion, shall we meet up to the next tower?”  “Sure thing, I will get my friends and be right there.”  I went back to my camp and told my friends of what happened and then we started up the path to the tower.  “Thank you much miss,” said Jerome, “It’s nothing, Jerome, Darkire, and Reana, this is Barggle(a smug looking jolly old dwarven warrior), Triton(a high-elf, looking of royalty, probably a paladin), and this is Shape,” she motioned to a barrel, the barrel started to change into an Erudite, a male of about six foot tall.  “Thanks once again for sharing your camp and food with us.”  I said.  “Ha, boy, tis nothing at all, for we have plenty and we are not short on ale if ye be hankering fer some..heh(hic), heh,” “I think ill take you up on the offer,” I said smiling.
	When I awoke Reana was sitting beside me, and Jerome was sitting across from me.  “Where are the others Jerome?”  They didn’t look to happy, “They have been gone for quite some time, along with our supplies,” I couldn’t believe it, I guess father was right, trust no one.  “Well at least we still have my money I kept hidden in my boot.  I pulled out the pouch with a few platinum, gold, and silver pieces.  “When we get to Highhold we can get more supplies, and if we meet up with our “friends” again we just might have to have a little talk with them.”  I always try to sound tough, but secretly I just hoped that a group of bandits got them along their way.
	We left the camp with our gear handy and started on our way up to the top of the mountain were we shall be able to sleep on a bed.  I smiled at the thought.  “Anyone have anything to drink?” said Jerome, “Yea I do, but it is ale,” I knew he did not like alcohol, but I offered it to him anyway.  He took a few sips then handed it back to me, “Thanks,” he said, I nodded to him.  “Well I think we are here,” and we stood in front of a large entrance made of rock, “Lets go inside.” I said anxiously.
	As we walked through we seen some of the citizens going in and out of some of the shops outside of the actual city, “ROAR,” I was knocked back with a hard blow, it was a gnoll, but much larger than that of a Blackburro gnoll, Reana was knocked down and being hit on by one of the gnolls, I started to get up but a gnoll started to cast something that made me drowsy, I collapsed and the gnoll started to beat on me, it looked as if Jerome was having the same problem.  “Come on, someone is in trouble,” someone shouted, and then the gnoll that was on me just disintegrated, by one spell that someone casted, then a huge Barbarian dug a large axe into the back of the one that was on Reana, and I very little person, a halfling it looked like, stabbed the gnoll that was on Jerome in the back and it just fell over, dead.  “Thank you sirs and madam,” I said, “You saved us,” they started muttering to each other and then looked harshly at us and the gnome, who had casted the spell that disintegrated the gnoll that was beating on me said, “You are lucky we were camped up at the top of that ridge or you would have been done for, fer sure.”  I resented that the gnome was so sure of himself, we could have beaten the gnolls if they hadn’t of sneaked up on us.  I thanked them and then me and my friends walked through a path and came to a building, I assumed it was an inn, but it was outside the actual city of Highhold.  We walked into the building, there was a bar in the middle of the room, and tables scattered out around the sides of the room.  I walked up to the bartender and asked, “Can we get a room here?”  The bartender just motioned up the stairs.  We walked up and there was another bar and I asked them the same question, “Yes you can get a room here, best prices for miles too,” said one of the female bartenders, she handed me a key and I paid her for it.  She took us down the hall, just smiling at us and showed us to our room.  She had also told us that there was a casino too.
	“Hey guys, I am gonna go check out this casino, I’ll be right back.”  I walked into the casino and seen a few tables with dealers standing behind them, and over in the corner of the room I seen an Erudite male, he wasn’t one of the people who robbed us, and he was handing platinum pieces over to the dealer with a worried look on his face.  His face….I recognized it, but didn’t know from where.  He glanced at me and stared squinty eyed at me and then his eyes widened, “Darkire?”, “How do you know my…….Judias, holy plaguebringer, I cant believe its you.”  I knew Judais from childhood, he lived in the aquaducts and he would come up top to kill some skeletons, for bone chips perhaps, and we got to know each other but just for about a year and then he disappeared, I knew his family rejected him because he wasn’t purely evil, even though he studied to become a shadow knight.  “Hey what brings you here?” Said my old friend, “I am on a quest to find my father, how about you why are you here?”  He looked ashamed, “I was thrown out of the guild of necromancers because I wouldn’t do sacrifices and worship cazic-thule, or innoruuk, or bertoxxulous, and I ended up here and lived here since then.  “You know what, I am traveling with some friends of mine, would you like to join us?” I asked eagerly, “Uh….sure….will they not mind that I use necromancy?”  “noooo, don’t worry about that,” I said with a smile, “follow me.”
	“What the…..he is evil I refuse to travel with such a person!” shouted Jerome, “Whoa. wait…calm down Jerome, he isn’t evil he just studies the dark arts,” I said, “Yes sire, I am agnostic, I have no feelings for any god, I just have been raised studying the dark arts and I am pretty good at it.” Said Judais with confidence.  “C’mon Jerome, what could it hurt to have another person watching our backs,” Reana who was quiet during the whole argument said, “I think we should let him join us, Jerome, can you put aside your differences and join forces?”  Jerome seemed angry, he nodded, and left the room.  “Judais and I are going to go inside Highhold, would you like to join us Reana?”  “No thank you, I will just stat here and wait on Jerome to come back,”  “Alright, bye,” and we left towards Highhold.  “Did you bring your battle gear?”  Judais asked, “Aye, I always carry it with me.”  He smiled, I must go to the bank real quick and grab my stuff, and we shall go gnoll hunting if you would like,” smile Judais, “Sure thing.” I said. </font></td>
	</tr>
